Package: SCdetMito
Title: Sample-Aware Adaptive Mitochondrial Quality Control for
        Single-Cell RNA-Seq
Version: 1.3.6
Authors@R: 
    person(
        given = "Silu",
        family = "Hu",
        role = c("aut", "cre"),
        email = "husilu0902@gmail.com"
    )
Description: SCdetMito provides sample-aware adaptive mitochondrial quality
    control for single-cell RNA-seq data. It constructs retained-cell profiles
    across candidate mitochondrial cutoffs, quantifies interval-specific cell
    loss, estimates sample-level mitochondrial cutoffs using robust
    retention-loss enrichment, and supports multi-sample QC strategies,
    benchmarking, sensitivity analysis, cutoff confidence reporting, and
    provenance tracking for Seurat workflows.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: ggplot2, reshape2, rlang, Seurat
Suggests: DoubletFinder, knitr, rmarkdown, SeuratData, testthat (>=
        3.0.0)
